certifications.title: NPTEL - Design And Analysis Of Algorithms

projects.name: Water Quality Prediction
projects.description: Developed a machine learning model to predict water quality metrics using a Kaggle dataset and applied various algorithms such as Linear Regression and Support Vector Machine (SVM), comparing their performance. Conducted comprehensive data preprocessing (cleaning, normalization, feature selection) to enhance model accuracy and reliability, and evaluated model performance using accuracy percentages and other metrics, achieving significant predictive accuracy. Utilized Python and essential libraries like Pandas, Scikit-learn, and Matplotlib for data analysis, model development, and result visualization.

projects.name: Early Detection and Prevention of Forest Fire
projects.description: Designed and implemented a prototype for early forest fire detection using a wireless network of ESP32 Microcontroller and DHT11 sensor to monitor environmental changes. Developed algorithms to analyze data collected from sensors, triggering alerts when temperatures exceeded predetermined safety thresholds. Successfully demonstrated the project at the Project Expo24, showcasing the functionality and potential impact on forest fire management and prevention strategies.
